    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>April 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental"><hi rend="italic">Private</hi></seg>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am sorry to say that I can be of no assistance to you.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> Any remarks which I might make on your letter would as far as they had any influence, add to your doubts on subjects which you consider sacred.</p>
<p>In my opinion every man ought to weigh for himself impartially &amp; anxiously all the arguments for &amp; against any revelation ever having been made to man.—</p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div> 
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
